this cut is surgical.

107
00:11:26,953 --> 00:11:30,790
Through the windpipe and
esophagus on the first cut.

108
00:11:30,791 --> 00:11:34,894
And the second deepens all the
way down to the spinal cord.

109
00:11:34,895 --> 00:11:36,896
RAY: Was he trying to get a trophy?

110
00:11:36,897 --> 00:11:41,199
Well, another cut and it
was his, so, I'd say no.

111
00:11:41,834 --> 00:11:43,502
What happened to the finger?

112
00:11:43,503 --> 00:11:46,105
SPERE: He broke it before she died.

113
00:11:46,106 --> 00:11:49,141
You can see the swelling.
That's definitely before.

114
00:11:49,142 --> 00:11:51,777
So she did fight back.

115
00:11:51,778 --> 00:11:55,014
It would be the only sign.
Didn't see anything else.

116
00:11:55,015 --> 00:11:58,417
RAY: Her face looked like she
was screaming when she died.

117
00:11:58,418 --> 00:12:02,822
That's a horror movie myth,
faces frozen in terror.

118
00:12:02,823 --> 00:12:04,523
Mostly the dead look drunk.

119
00:12:04,524 --> 00:12:06,959
This was clearly manipulated.

120
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:10,963
You have to wait until rigor
mortis sets in, about three hours.

121
00:12:10,964 --> 00:12:13,632
And then, you have to
hold the mouth and tongue

122
00:12:13,633 --> 00:12:16,502
in that position until
the muscle sets.

123
00:12:16,503 --> 00:12:18,704
For how long?

124
00:12:18,705 --> 00:12:20,940
I'd say another hour.

125
00:12:20,941 --> 00:12:24,742
He was standing over her with
his fingers in her mouth.

126
00:12:26,679 --> 00:12:30,983
When I was a taxidermist I actually
tried it on this tabby cat, and I...

127
00:12:30,984 --> 00:12:32,950
(CLEARS THROAT)

128
00:12:33,819 --> 00:12:35,654
We're not equipped for this,

129
00:12:35,655 --> 00:12:38,190
and you are in no shape
to be chasing anyone.

130
00:12:38,191 --> 00:12:41,060
That leaves me. This is something
I can't handle on my own.

131
00:12:41,061 --> 00:12:43,496
What, are you complaining about
this before we even give it a try?

132
00:12:43,497 --> 00:12:45,531
We need to get Mason to
assign a homicide detective.

133
00:12:45,532 --> 00:12:47,466
We are detectives.
This is our town.

134
00:12:47,467 --> 00:12:49,602
- Don't let your personal shit
cloud your judgment.
- We can do this.

135
00:12:49,603 --> 00:12:51,103
- What are you talking about?
- Your words.

136
00:12:51,104 --> 00:12:52,805
- I don't understand what
you're talking about.
- Your words.

137
00:12:52,806 --> 00:12:56,675
I don't understand. All I have to say is
I'm gonna do this with or without you.

138
00:12:56,676 --> 00:12:59,777
So if I have to, I'll do it alone.

139
00:13:04,216 --> 00:13:06,552
Fuck you, Hazel.

140
00:13:06,553 --> 00:13:09,954
Thanks. I knew you'd get onboard.

141
00:13:14,693 --> 00:13:16,627
What?

142
00:13:18,798 --> 00:13:22,433
I don't think you get this
good on the first try.

143
00:13:24,003 --> 00:13:26,070
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

144
00:13:35,681 --> 00:13:37,648
(DISTORTED NOISES)

145
00:13:39,852 --> 00:13:41,952
BOY: Over here.

146
00:13:45,858 --> 00:13:48,359
Move back. Give her some space.

147
00:13:50,262 --> 00:13:52,096
(DOOR CLOSING)

148
00:13:59,338 --> 00:14:01,640
I heard about Delia.

149
00:14:01,641 --> 00:14:03,776
Oh, that was fast. Who told you?

150
00:14:03,777 --> 00:14:05,211
Trudy Davis.

151
00:14:05,212 --> 00:14:07,112
Everybody's over at the church.

152
00:14:07,113 --> 00:14:09,114
Why aren't you there?

153
00:14:09,115 --> 00:14:12,251
'Cause I wanted to be
here when you got home.

154
00:14:12,252 --> 00:14:15,052
Well, I'm home, so you can go.

155
00:14:16,288 --> 00:14:18,524
You know, it would mean
a lot to everybody if...

156
00:14:18,525 --> 00:14:23,229
Oh, please, do not start with
your Sundays of sunshine shit.

157
00:14:23,230 --> 00:14:25,898
You can knock it all you want,

158
00:14:25,899 --> 00:14:28,534
but when you were in the hospital
they were there for you.

159
00:14:28,535 --> 00:14:31,237
I didn't ask them to be there
for me. It was my back,

160
00:14:31,238 --> 00:14:34,340
and they made it into some
kind of community tragedy.

161
00:14:34,341 --> 00:14:35,674
It wasn't just your back.

162
00:14:35,675 --> 00:14:37,975
You were about to have a baby.

163
00:14:41,380 --> 00:14:42,948
Well, that was a long time ago.

164
00:14:42,949 --> 00:14:44,450
And I can count on one hand

165
00:14:44,451 --> 00:14:46,418
the number of times
you've talked about it.

166
00:14:46,419 --> 00:14:49,854
All right, look, I will
go to the funeral. Okay?

167
00:14:53,292 --> 00:14:55,127
What do you want to eat?

168
00:14:55,128 --> 00:14:57,029
Nothing. I'm going out.

169
00:14:57,030 --> 00:14:59,263
- With who?
- With Andy.

170
00:15:00,432 --> 00:15:02,533
Will his wife be there?

171
00:15:02,534 --> 00:15:04,835
Oh, I hope so.

172
00:15:05,404 --> 00:15:07,338
(CHUCKLES)

173
00:15:15,748 --> 00:15:17,549
Hey. Sorry I'm late.

174
00:15:17,550 --> 00:15:19,952
I was starving. I went ahead.

175
00:15:19,953 --> 00:15:21,587
I got you a drink.

176
00:15:21,588 --> 00:15:23,354
Thanks.

177
00:15:24,957 --> 00:15:26,857
(SIGHING)

178
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:36,168
What's going on? You okay?

179
00:15:36,169 --> 00:15:37,903
It's this back.

180
00:15:37,904 --> 00:15:41,740
I gotta have an operation for
the, you know, disk thing.

181
00:15:41,741 --> 00:15:44,310
Again? What about the shots?

182
00:15:44,311 --> 00:15:46,045
They're not working.

183
00:15:46,046 --> 00:15:48,681
One doctor says it's autoimmune.

184
00:15:48,682 --> 00:15:50,783
The other one says it was
the original operation.

185
00:15:50,784 --> 00:15:51,951
I don't know.

186
00:15:51,952 --> 00:15:54,486
- When do they want you to have it?
- Six months ago.

187
00:15:54,487 --> 00:15:57,022
Oh, Hazel.

188
00:15:57,023 --> 00:15:59,491
I mean, your stubbornness
is gonna kill you.

189
00:15:59,492 --> 00:16:01,826
There's worse ways to go.

190
00:16:03,595 --> 00:16:06,765
Listen, there's a great rehabilitation
facility. It's in North Bay.

191
00:16:06,766 --> 00:16:08,667
Are you crazy? I'm not
leaving my house.

192
00:16:08,668 --> 00:16:10,135
Your mom can't carry you.

193
00:16:10,136 --> 00:16:13,571
(LAUGHS) I'd like to see her try.

194
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:16,342
(SIGHS)

195
00:16:16,343 --> 00:16:21,111
Maybe I can help some. I could come
over maybe once or twice a day.

196
00:16:23,415 --> 00:16:25,649
What would your wife say?

197
00:16:26,085 --> 00:16:27,820
(LAUGHS) My wife?

198
00:16:27,821 --> 00:16:30,389
My wife would say that
you're having surgery

199
00:16:30,390 --> 00:16:32,756
to get me under your roof again.

200
00:16:33,258 --> 00:16:35,292
(LAUGHING)

201
00:16:39,798 --> 00:16:41,932
She's a riot.

202
00:16:42,334 --> 00:16:44,036
BARTENDER: Here you go, Hazel.

203
00:16:44,037 --> 00:16:45,871
You two seem to be in sync.

204
00:16:45,872 --> 00:16:47,805
You jealous?

205
00:16:50,109 --> 00:16:52,209
(CELL PHONE VIBRATES)

206
00:16:57,082 --> 00:16:58,550
You gotta go.

207
00:16:58,551 --> 00:17:00,618
No, I should go.

208
00:17:00,853 --> 00:17:02,653
I should go, Hazel.

209
00:17:03,255 --> 00:17:06,390
I'll... I'll get you next time.

210
00:17:08,327 --> 00:17:12,131
Wait. I mean, while
I have you here,

211
00:17:12,132 --> 00:17:13,699
I just thought maybe you
could help me with this.

212
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:16,934
This asshole cop got me on
the way back from hockey.

213
00:17:20,706 --> 00:17:22,573
Sure.

214
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:25,709
- Okay, thanks.
- Mmm-hmm.

215
00:17:26,979 --> 00:17:28,812
Okay.

216
00:18:04,450 --> 00:18:08,419
We don't open for a couple
of minutes, but come on in.

217
00:18:10,589 --> 00:18:13,325
It's cold. Hmm.

218
00:18:13,326 --> 00:18:17,061
Have a seat wherever you like.
Coffee's brewing.

219
00:18:24,536 --> 00:18:27,638
Some hot water, if you have it.

220
00:18:40,686 --> 00:18:43,554
That one of those green teas?

221
00:18:44,022 --> 00:18:45,956
It's damiana,

222
00:18:46,291 --> 00:18:47,759
natural tonic.

223
00:18:47,760 --> 00:18:49,727
Oh.

224
00:18:52,664 --> 00:18:54,666
